p=21>2</a> </td><td align=right> <br><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showMessage?topicID=417.topic"> << Prev Topic </a> &nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showMessage?topicID=392.topic"> Next Topic >> </a> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=95%><tr><td bgcolor=#CCCCCC><table border=0 width=100% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top bgcolor=#8B0000 class=headings><font color=#000000>Author</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=#8B0000 class=headings><font color=#000000>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usymphonieorchestra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Symphonie Orchestra</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/4/01 5:30:17 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Weapons Training</span><hr size=1> Lately I have been using a two hand blunt staff to build my skill with it which, got me to thinking...How many Warriors take the time to train in all weapons (one and two hand slash,one and two hand blunt and piercing.)??? <p>Symphonie Orchestra
<BR>44 Gnome Warrior
<BR>The Valkyries of Norrath(Eci)
<BR>EQ's all women guild.
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugreblaja.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Greblaja</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/4/01 7:46:50 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://cx227738-a.ports1.ri.home.com/everquest/ogbar06.gif height=260 width=130></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapons Training</span><hr size=1> I am of the opinion that every warrior should learn them all.  It is a shame to not use a great weapon later on in your career because your skill is so low that you fear you wont be helping your group by using it.  Of course, I was a 1hs/2hs guy myself for most of my career, so I had to learn the hard lesson of how to skill up later in life.  Right now, my piercing is my lowest, at 178 or so, at lvl 49.<br>
<br>
The key is to find low delay weapons with which to practice all of you skills - low delay equals more swings per fight equals more chances to skill up.  I have started a variety of blade swinging classes and have found that you can easily keep three weapon skills maxed by around lvl 10, and four by around lvl 15.  Keeping all five maxed by around 20 and beyond should not be that difficult. <p>-G<P>
<IMG SRC="http://cx227738-a.ports1.ri.home.com/everquest/modsquad.gif" border=0></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwarninwraithlore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Warnin Wraithlore</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.telusplanet.net/public/canadak/sig.JPG BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/5/01 2:51:19 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.telusplanet.net/public/canadak/warnin1.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapons Training</span><hr size=1> I do them all as well.  I learned the hard way as well with my paladin not working up 1hb and 2hb.  Even with my warrior I neglected a few at the start and they are now hard to raise.  I need a good group with a few other tanks to raise the low ones, basically where my damage is not needed as much.  <br>
<br>
We are warriors, the masters of weaponry.  I think we should work them all up, besides you never know what the next uber weapon is gonna be.  Imagine getting to level 40 and finding a really cool 1hb and not being able to use it cause your 1hb skill is 4.  <br>
<br>
stick with it, it is a pain until the 20s then you have more than enough time to work them all up. And if you have fast weapons it only takes a few minutes.<br>
<br>
be well! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=furns>FURNs</A></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/5/01 3:15:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapons Training</span><hr size=1> Every melee class should have all weapon skills maxed.<br>
<br>
I always trained 1HS 2HS and piercing in lvl 38 i started with 2HB with a slow weapon 5 lvls later i had it maxed, a few days ago i started with 1HB (at lvl 45) i had a skill of 30 (dumped points in it) a guy lend me his blackjack a 7/21 weapon - so a real fast one - in 3 hours with celerity i had a skill of 105...so it worked great, hope he lends it to me again soon o)<br>
<br>
Happy hunting<br>
<br>
Furn <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uowynabhaya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Owyn Abhaya</A></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/5/01 7:13:38 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapons Training</span><hr size=1> Speaking of, what methods do you use? My warrior just hit 30. Right now, 1hs and 1hb are maxxed. 2hs is about 20 points behind, and 2hb is about 30 points behind. I've been dumping a few points into piercing, but I haven't really worked on it yet in combat. <br>
<br>
Here's what I've been doing at each level. Start with 1hs. Get it maxxed. Switch to 1hb, max that. Then switch to 2hs. I've been thinking that I'll focus on one at a time until I max it out. I know this must be purely perception on my part, but it seems like the longer I hold the weapon in my hand, the more frequently the improvements come (as opposed to swapping between weapons frequently). <br>
<br>
Is this valid thinking, or should I swap between weapons after each point of skill improvement? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udraky.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Draky</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/5/01 9:14:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapons Training</span><hr size=1> I used only 1H slashing and 2H slashing exclusivly till level 52 (was maxed out 50 before Kunark). Now at 57 I've all my weapons skills within 8 points of being maxed out. Don't worry about maxing out your weapons skill till you have to I say. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>The Caitiff of The Rathe</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uyildabodacious.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yilda Bodacious</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/ez_icons/emoticons/laugh.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/5/01 9:18:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapons Training</span><hr size=1> I quit worrying about 2HS after getting ahold of a Staff of Battle (2HB, 31/37), as there really arent many 2HS weapons that are better.  For the few that are, there are also 2HB that are equal to them.<br>
<br>
I also dont worry about 1HB, as with 1HS and Piercing, I have all the weapons I could ever need and I am very happy with the weapons I have and dont need to go out looking for a 2HS or 1HB that is better than what I already posses. <p><CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 BGCOLOR="#FFCC00" CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH=191><TR><TD COLSPAN=2><P ALIGN=CENTER><B><FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Comic Sans MS,Tekton,Blueprint,Dom Casual,Dom Casual BT">Yilda Bodacious</FONT></B></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH=100><img src="http://yilda.50megs.com/yildacob.gif"></TD><TD WIDTH=249><embed src="http://www.pimpit.com/images/enter.swf" quality=high pluginspage="http://www.macromedia.com/shockwave/download/index.cgi?P1_Prod_Version=ShockwaveFlash" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="249" height="249" align="left"></embed></TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN=2><P ALIGN=CENTER><B><FONT COLOR="#6699FF" SIZE="-1" FACE="Comic Sans MS,Tekton,Blueprint,Dom Casual,Dom Casual BT">54 Gnome Warrior of The Companions</FONT></B></TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN=2><P ALIGN=CENTER><B><FONT COLOR="#FFFFCC" SIZE="-1" FACE="Comic Sans MS,Tekton,Blueprint,Dom Casual,Dom Casual BT">The Tribunal</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugaryen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Garyen</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.houseofdarklight.com/other/g.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>is a Seasoned Veteran</b><br>  Posts: 266<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/5/01 11:44:59 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/classes/c_warrior.gif width=71 height=177></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapons Training</span><hr size=1> a warrior that can't use 1handed weapons? <p><p align="left"><b>-garyen varillious al'dar<br>
