<br>
<img src="http://www.houseofdarklight.com/GARISABEAST.jpg" border="0" width="320" height="240"></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uiuldiin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iuldiin</A></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/5/01 3:04:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapons Training</span><hr size=1> I think you should keep em all maxed... only things that are lacking are: 2hb at 150ish and h2h <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  at about 12... <p>-Iuldiin</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukazarksnaketongue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kazark Snaketongue</A></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/6/01 8:36:35 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapons Training</span><hr size=1> Max all skills so you don't have to worry about it later.  Use one weapon type in main hand and a different weapon type in off hand.  Once main hand weapon gets capped for level switch your off hand into main hand and get another weapon type for off hand.  Confusing eh?  This will ensure all your one handed weapons stay capped.  Also once your one handed weapons are done with level cap get your 2 handers capped.  You should be able to have all weapons capped by level 40.  Then post 50 you'll start seeing an increase in skills again.  Repeat process.<br>
<br>
Kazark Snaketongue, 55 Iksar Soldier<br>
 Member of Arcis on Povar<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> kremlar</span><br> <b>is too scared to Register</b><br>   <font color=#FF0000>(3/8/01 3:46:30 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   skillz</span><hr size=1> 1hb and piercing you can pretty much ignore for a while, you can put them in your offhand and just so long as you have a good 1hs to offset the damage you'll be fine. velium weapons work well enough.<br>
<br>
2hb i'm still puzzling over a decent way to train up, dumped 50 some points into it cause i've got nothing better to spend them on but can't do much in combat training cause the damage blows. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usymphonieorchestra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Symphonie Orchestra</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/8/01 10:43:00 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Weapons training - 2hb</span><hr size=1> I guess it all depends on the weapon your using Kremlar and if ya got haste in buffs or items. I wasn't even thinking 2hb at all till a guildie lent me a Stormwood Battle Staff which has decent dmg/dly and a 96 dd proc. Even a at skill of 40 I realized that 2hb can do some serious damage even unhasted. I still have not even tried 1hb but started looking at tranquil canes and wondering what they could do to a maxed 1hb player. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubearogfrostborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bearog Frostborn</A></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/15/01 9:56:09 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapons training - 2hb</span><hr size=1> Me maxed 1hs 2hs Piercing H2H.  There are bashing weapons that are nice, but I chose my road and its pierce or slash.<br>
<br>
Yake a look at the crafted velium War Lance....2hp, uses same skill base as piercing.  one of the new lances is like 32dam and 39dly or there abouts.<br>
<br>
Jarsith Trident...cana ya say piercing nice?<br>
<br>
<br>
There are better I'm sure, dont claim ta be no expert on tha matta.  I bash alright, with my fist thats about it.<br>
<br>
BTW 2hs is important...look at the stats of Sunderfury...800+hp DPM minimum.  Axe of Lost Souls, Palladium etc.  Then when ya get yer epic ua just gonna dual weild em? nah, 2hs against DS criters.<br>
<br>
My 2cp worth.<br>
<br>
Bear <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utalicmoore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talic Moore</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/15/01 10:31:16 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.darkageofcamelot.com/concept/elfw.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapons Training</span><hr size=1> It's very important to train in all your weapons skills (I myself have maxed all of them and continue to do so with each level) <br>
<br>
Yilda posted:<br>
 &quot;I quit worrying about 2HS after getting ahold of a Staff of Battle (2HB, 31/37), as there really arent many 2HS weapons that are better. For the few that are, there are also 2HB that are equal to them.&quot;<br>
<br>
Actually, there is now a two-handed sword that drops in Hate with that damage/delay and stats. There are lots of weapons of all types and each can cater to a specific situation, so I would recommend training in everything you can get. After all, what are you gonna do if you pick up an awesome spear somewhere and can't tell one end from the other? <p>Talic Asaria Moore--
Kalrathi Blademasters--
Bristlebane Server--
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugristlebone.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GristleBone</A></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/15/01 12:12:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapons Training</span><hr size=1> I didn't worry about maxing my skills till the mid 40s... at 50th Pierce, 1hs, 2hs, 1hb are all max and 2hb is 173. Instead of trying to get a good weapon of each type, just get fast ones... for instance 3/19 combine daggers for pierce.<br>
<br>
Most groups in the outdoor Kunark zones will let you practice on their pulls so long as you don't KS... it benefits both of you as they get free damage and you get skill increases. Once you get the skill to a respectable level try to get weapons that don't decrease your damage output too badly and sneak them in when the group isn't struggling.<br>
<br>
Gristlebone <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umorphiusthejeweller.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MorphiusTheJeweller</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/15/01 12:23:58 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapons Training</span><hr size=1> When you get Riposte disc at 56 you will wish you had kept up your 2hb or 2hs skills. <p><center><img src="http://www.darkcrimson.net/pics/morphl.jpg" border=0></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uyildabodacious.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yilda Bodacious</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/ez_icons/emoticons/laugh.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/15/01 12:48:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapons Training</span><hr size=1> How often do you all find yourself using 2Handed anything?  The only use I have for them is if there is a dmg shield (and I will switch back as soon as its dispelled to 1hs) or using riposte disc.  Other than those 2 situations, I will always dual wield. <p><CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 BGCOLOR="#FFCC00" CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH=191><TR><TD COLSPAN=2><P ALIGN=CENTER><B><FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Comic Sans MS,Tekton,Blueprint,Dom Casual,Dom Casual BT">Yilda Bodacious</FONT></B></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH=100><img src="http://www.users.qwest.net/~jlarson2/yildacob.gif"></TD><TD WIDTH=249><embed src="http://www.pimpit.com/images/enter.swf" quality=high pluginspage="http://www.macromedia.com/shoc